<br>
Had the break in at the zone. using AoE. I was the only one of the AoE group who survived. Must be because at 55 I was the lowest level and never got summoned by the second floor.<br>
<br>
Second AoE pull came to us at SS. We werent prepared so most of the raid died. After that It went nice. Seen better, seen worse. We started on second floor whith less people. Main tanks died in no time on a 3 pull. Chanters too and I was trying to get some mana back while at 10% Hp. Finally I was able to get 3 lures through in the end thereby getting the last one down which was being tanked by rangers bards and druids. At that moment we decided to get out.<br>
<br>
So, the diamond rod drops from minibosses. Was hoping on an eye though.<br>
<br>
Also people do not understand what Translocating from HATE means. Took way to long to set up a melee group for a grouptranslocate. And one of those Foolish assholes even declined the TL to bind because he wanted to go to the dreadlands. One day I will really leave those assholes behind there. <br>
<br>
The reason I go to HATE is because it is fun to see and I like the excitement. There is simply no loot to speak off and the xp is not always there. especially if they decide to split the wizards between groups. I like to get the killshots on Spitegolems though, makes me feel like a wizard again. <p><center>There used to be a signature here, but the site hosting it, my provider, decided to delete all personal homepage directories.<br><table><tr>
